Lampert Capital Markets Appoints Tobias Lenza as Managing Director and Head of Equity Capital Markets | Business Wire
























































Lampert Capital Markets Appoints Tobias Lenza as Managing Director 
      and Head of Equity Capital Markets






February 27, 2014 11:47 AM Eastern Standard Time



NEW YORK--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Lampert Capital Markets, Inc. announced today that Tobias Lenza has been 
      appointed as Managing Director - Equity Capital Markets. Mr. Lenza will 
      spearhead the firm’s expansion into providing a differentiated equity 
      product to institutional and retail investors on managed offerings as 
      well as formalize syndicate relationships with key investment banks.
    


      Lenza brings nearly two decades of experience in equity sales and 
      trading. Mr. Lenza served as a NASDAQ market maker responsible for over 
      100 securities as Head Trader of Savant Trading. Since that time, Mr. 
      Lenza has been actively involved in equity capital markets at a number 
      of firms engaging in both public and private equity transactions. 
      According to Eric Schweitzer, Chief Operating Officer, “Toby brings a 
      traders’ sense of timing and an investors’ sense of value to every 
      transaction...qualities that will inure to the benefit of each of our 
      equity capital market’s clients.”
    

      “Toby Lenza’s wealth of experience, expertise and industry knowledge has 
      made him a key member of our team,” said Randy Lampert, CEO of Lampert 
      Capital Markets. “His appointment signals our burgeoning commitment to 
      create a new and proprietary approach to the Equity Capital Markets, in 
      general, and primary equity offerings, in particular. As importantly, 
      Toby embodies the qualities of integrity, candor and respectful behavior 
      that characterize Lampert Capital Markets’ approach to clients and 
      employees, alike.”
    

About Lampert Capital Markets


      Lampert Capital Markets, Inc. is an investment bank providing 
      proprietary financing options and investing opportunities to private 
      investors, institutions and corporations. LCM provides a broad range of 
      services including high net worth retail and institutional fixed income 
      and equity sales, institutional trading and fundraising services and 
      financial advisory and corporate finance services. Lampert Capital 
      Markets is a subsidiary of Lampert Debt Advisors, an institutional debt 
      advisory firm meeting the debt financing needs of private equity 
      portfolio companies, entrepreneurially-backed companies and public 
      growth companies. Both firms share a common foundation built on trust, 
      integrity, candor and fair dealing with customers, clients and employees.
    


Contacts

      Lampert Capital Markets, Inc.S. Randy Lampert, 646-833-4900Presidentwww.lampertcm.com


















